<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="566" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1079,1319]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1079,1104]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons broad, sunken; ocellar and fronto-orbital bristles absent; postvertical, inner and outer vertical bristles present; face with rounded tubercle; arista bare; 
<number box="[783,797,1116,1140]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" value="1.0">1</number>
postpronotal bristle; posterior thoracic spiracle with 
<number box="[1394,1436,1116,1140]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
bristles; scutellum weakly concave dorsally, setulose on disc with 
<number box="[899,940,1151,1175]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
pairs of discal bristles, in addition to apical bristles; hind tibiae strongly flattened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
